'''Donald Adam''' is a former [[New Zealand]] [[rowing (sport)|rower]]. 
At the [[1950 British Empire Games]] he won the [[silver medal]] as part of the men's eight alongside crew members [[Kerry Ashby]], [[Murray Ashby]], [[Bruce Culpan]], [[Thomas Engel]], [[Grahame Jarratt]], [[Don Rowlands]], [[Edwin Smith (rower)|Edwin Smith]] and [[Bill Tinnock]].

