== Prognosis and treatment ==
Prognosis is highly variable and dependent upon a multitude of factors. Reoccurrence does occur.<ref name=pmid19346063>{{cite journal |vauthors=May M, Brookman-Amissah S, Roigas J |title=Prognostic Accuracy of Individual Uropathologists in Noninvasive Urinary Bladder Carcinoma: A Multicentre Study Comparing the 1973 and 2004 World Health Organisation Classifications |journal=Eur. Urol. |volume= 57|issue= 5|pages= 850–8|date=March 2009 |pmid=19346063 |doi=10.1016/j.eururo.2009.03.052 |url=|display-authors=etal}}</ref> Treatment is determined on a case-by-case basis.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Babjuk|first1=M.|last2=Oosterlinck|first2=W.|last3=Sylveste|first3=R.|last4=Kaasinen|first4=E.|last5=Böhle|first5=A.|last6=Palou-Redorta|first6=J.|last7=Rouprêt|first7=M.|title=EAU guidelines on non-muscle-invasive urothelial carcinoma of the bladder, the 2011 update|journal=Actas Urológicas Españolas (English Edition)|date=July–August 201|volume=36|issue=7|pages=389–402|doi=10.1016/j.acuroe.2011.12.007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
| title = Bladder cancer treatment; invasive cancer
| url = http://www.uptodate.com/contents/bladder-cancer-treatment-invasive-cancer-beyond-the-basics
| accessdate = 2015-03-04
}}
</ref>
